href="/store/apps/details?id=factory.widgets.ThreeDDigitalWeatherClock" title="3D Digital Weather Clock"> 39.    3D Digital Weather Clock  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.ThreeDDigitalWeatherClock"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaMwoxEi8KKWZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5UaHJlZUREaWdpdGFsV2VhdGhlckNsb2NrEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  A 3D Digital Weather Clock widget with size 4x2<br>It features:<p>* 12/24 hour clock<br>* Color choice on some info displayed<br>* System Stats Information pop-up<br>* Battery icon on clock<br>* Week number in the hours tab, as an option<br>* for scheduling outdoor activities - Sunrise /Sunset times in the forecast screen,as an option in the configuration screen.<br>* for scheduling outdoor activities - Day length and hours left in the forecast screen,as an option in the configuration screen.<br>* Weather information with icon, current temperature and high low temperature for the day on the clock face.<br>* Detailed 4 day weather forecast screen with forecast temperature,high low temperature and condition description for each day.<br>* 2 Forecast layouts</p><p>Features the following hotspots:<br> tap bottom right-&gt;back to configuration screen<br> tap bottom left-&gt;Launch system information window<br> tap on weather icon-&gt;Launch weather forecast screen<br> tap Hour-&gt;launch anything!(set your own preference from configuration screen)<br> tap Min -&gt;launch anything!(set your own preference from configuration screen)</p><p>Widgets on Android work a bit differently than a normal application. Unlike regular programs they don't just install themselves in the application tray so you have to add them manually. They will not open or launch.<br>Here's how to add a widget on your Android home screen.</p><p>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger. <br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets. <br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device. <br>4.Select the "3D Digital Weather Clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>"Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.</p><p>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD WIDGETS<br>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DpMLF9b2aTQ</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=factory.widgets.ThreeDDigitalWeatherClock" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </div> </div>     <div class="reason-set">  <span key features are listed below:<br>- Current conditions and sunrise, sunset<br>- 7-day forecast and 3-hr forecast<br>- 7-day temperature chart.<br>- Tidal forecast<br>- Radar (with Google map)<br>- Sense Analog Clock Widget  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.SenseClock"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaJAoiEiAKGmZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5TZW5zZUNsb2NrEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Android Digital clock widget with Calendar, Time, System info,weather &amp; forecast<p>Sense cross Analog style clock,size 4x2</p><p>A Digital Clock widget with size 4x2<br>It features:<br>============<br>140 skins<br>12/24 hour + Color choice on all info displayed<br>System Stats Info + pop-up<br>Moon phase icon<br>Weather &amp; Forecast<br>2 Weather layouts on clock(user choice)<br>2 Forecast layouts(user choice)<br>Sunrise/Suntime times and calculations</p><p>Interactivity<br>=============<br>+tap bottom right-&gt;preferences<br>+tap bottom left-&gt;system information dialog<br>+tap weather icon-&gt;forecast<br>+tap Hour-&gt;launch anything!<br>+tap Minutes-&gt;launch anything!</p><p>Widgets General<br>===============<br>Widgets on Android work a bit differently than a normal application. Unlike regular programs they don't just install themselves in the application tray so you have to add them manually. They will not open or launch.<br>Here's how to add a widget on your Android home screen.</p><p>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger.<br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets.<br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device.<br>4.Select the "3D Digital Weather Clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Steps how to add a widget (ICS Android 4.0) <br>==========================================<br>On any Home screen, touch the All Apps icon located in the center of the Favorites tray. Then select the Widgets tab and touch &amp; hold a widget.<br>Drag and drop the widget on a screen with empty space.<br>If the widget is not visible under the widgets tab in the application drawer,restart your phone and it will appear. <br>under the tab widgets. <br>Touch &amp; hold a widget, then drag and drop it on a screen with empty space.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>"Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.</p><p>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD WIDGETS<br>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DpMLF9b2aTQ</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span href="/store/apps/details?id=jp.co.rcsc.yurekuru.android" title="yurekuru call"> 92.    yurekuru call  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=RC+Solution+Co." title="RC Solution Co.">RC Solution Co.</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="jp.co.rcsc.yurekuru.android"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaJQojEiEKG2pwLmNvLnJjc2MueXVyZWt1cnUuYW5kcm9pZBABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  This is a push notification app. which gives you a notice of the earthquake warning with an estimated seismic intensity (the Japanese seven-stage seismic scale) and arrival time of the tremor to the specific location where you registered.<p>[Initial settings]<br>Register the prediction point and the seismic intensity threshold.<br>The prediction point is a place where you want to receive the earthquake warning for. The seismic intensity threshold is the standard value. This app. gives you a notice when the estimated seismic intensity is lower than the registered threshold.</p><p>[More about this app.]<br>This app. works with the Earthquake Early Warning (EEW) for advanced users which delivered by the Japan Meteorological Agency (JMA). This means that, when receiving the EEW from the JMA, this application will give you a notice each time. The EEW for the advanced users has a characteristic which derivers warning several times for each earthquake with improving the precision of a seismic intensity. So, this app. may give you several notices with different estimated seismic intensity and arrival time.<br>Also, with this app. you can view the information of earthquakes occurred in the past. </p><p>[Note]<br>1.The estimated seismic intensity may yield a slight error by less than 1.</p><p>2.In the case below, the notice of the earthquake warning may delay or failed.<br>The prediction point and the seismic intensity threshold are not registered.<br>The registered prediction point is close to the epicenter.<br>The trouble in network.<br>The distance between the registered prediction point and the epicenter is more than 2000 kilometers.<br>The depth of the epicenter is more than 150 kilometers.<br>Due to the Maintenance of the server.<br>Too much load on the server.<br>EEW is not delivered by JMA.</p><p>3.Twitter Service is not available, you can not view the information of earthquakes occurred in the past. </p><p>4.This app. is designed for use in Japan only.</p><p>5.To know more about the Earthquake Early Warning, see the JMA homepage.</p><p>[Requrements]<br>Android 2.3</p><p>[facebook page]<br>http://www.facebook.com/yurekuru</p><p>[developer's blog]<br>http://rcsc.hatenablog.com</p><p>[FAQ]<br>http://support.rcsc.co.jp/support/yurekuru_faq.html</p><p>has an FAQ on facebook page</p><p>[Information]<br>information@rcsc.co.jp</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=jp.co.rcsc.yurekuru.android" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </div> </div>     <div class="reason-set">  <span class="stars-container"> <a It may take a couple minutes for it to appear on the watch due to the number of high resolution images. After the installation is complete, open the handheld app to customize the look of your watch face. Then set the Weather Time watch face on your watch.</p><p><br>Free Features and Options<br>  3 different weather providers to choose from<br> Weather data for current location or fixed location<br>  7 fixed background images and colors<br> Color picker to choose any background, foreground, and shadow color<br>  Color picker to choose any foreground color for ambient mode<br> Display temperature in variable height notification cards<br>  Option for translucent notification cards<br>  Option to hide notification cards in ambient mode<br>  5-10 day forecast (depending on chosen weather provider)</p><p>Premium Features and Options (Requires 1 time in app purchase)<br>  Set any image on your phone as your watch background<br> Set how long the screen stays awake before dimming or Display current temp with next calendar event<br>  Display current temp with wind, pressure, and humidity<br> Display high/low, short term forecast, or upcoming forecast along with current temp</p><p><br>3 ways to open the weather forecast:<br>* Tap on the home screen and say "Ok, Google, start weather forecast"<br>* Tap on the home screen, scroll down to "Start..." and find the Weather Sense Analog Clock Widget Dark  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.SenseClockDark"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaKAomEiQKHmZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5TZW5zZUNsb2NrRGFyaxABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Android Digital clock widget with Calendar, Time, System info,weather &amp; forecast<p>Sense cross Analog Dark style clock,size 4x2</p><p>It features:<br>============<br> 212 skins to choose from<br> 12 or 24 hour mode<br> Portrait or Landscape mode<br> Color choice for all information displayed on the widget<br> System Information on the widget front or as a pop-up window<br> Shows battery level on the widget<br> Shows Moon phase on the widget thats is calculated automatically each day.<br> Current Weather conditions which include:<br>+Current temperature in Fahrenheit or Celsius<br>+Feels like Temperature<br>+Humidity<br>+Wind speed in Km or miles per hour<br> 2 Weather layouts on clock widget(user selected from configuration screen)<br> 2 Forecast layouts(user selected from configuration screen)<br> 4 Day weather forecast that includes for each day:<br>+High and Low temperature<br>+Precipitation percentage<br>+Weather description<br> Sunrise/Sunset times in either Forecast screens<br> 37 unique weather condition icons<br> Widget hotspots for interaction<br>+tap bottom right widget corner-&gt;return to configuration screen<br>+tap bottom left widget corner-&gt;popup system information window<br>+tap weather icon-&gt;launch forecast screen<br>+tap Hours tab-&gt;launch anything!(user selected from configuration screen)<br>+tap Minutes tab-&gt;launch anything!(user selected from configuration screen)</p><p><br>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger.<br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets.<br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device.<br>4.Select the "3D Digital Weather Clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>- "Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>- When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.<br>- "Cannot find/Cannot Open/Cannot Launch"-&gt; read instructions above how to add widgets on your home screen, or step by step instructions in your application drawer.</p><p>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD WIDGETS<br>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DpMLF9b2aTQ</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a href="/store/apps/details?id=factory.widgets.MIUIDigitalClock" title="MIUI Digital Weather Clock"> 136.    MIUI Digital Weather Clock  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.MIUIDigitalClock"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaKgooEiYKIGZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5NSVVJRGlnaXRhbENsb2NrEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  MIUI Digital Weather Clock size 4x2<p>It features:<br>12/24 hr+Color on all info displayed<br>System Stats Info + pop-up<br>Weather &amp; Forecast<br>2 Forecast layouts(user choice)<br>+tap bottom right-&gt;preferences<br>+tap bottom left-&gt;system information dialog<br>+tap weather icon-&gt;forecast<br>+tap Hour-&gt;launch anything!(more coming)<br>+tap Minutes-&gt;launch anything!</p><p>WIDGETS GENERAL<br>===============<br>Widgets on Android work a bit differently than a normal application. Unlike regular programs they don't just install themselves in the application tray so you have to add them manually. They will not open or launch.<br>Here's how to add a widget on your Android home screen.</p><p>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger.<br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets.<br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device.<br>4.Select the clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>"Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.</p><p>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD WIDGETS<br>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DpMLF9b2aTQ</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a href="/store/apps/details?id=factory.widgets.SenseClock24" title="Sense Analog Clock Widget 24"> 169.    Sense Analog Clock Widget 24  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.SenseClock24"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaJgokEiIKHGZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5TZW5zZUNsb2NrMjQQARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Android Digital clock widget Calendar, Time, System info,weather &amp; forecast<p>A Digital Clock widget with size 4x2<br>It features:<br>212 skins<br>12/24 hr+Color on all info displayed<br>System Stats Info + pop-up<br>Weather &amp; Forecast<br>2 Weather layouts on clock(user choice)<br>2 Forecast layouts(user choice)<br>+tap bottom right-&gt;preferences<br>+tap bottom left-&gt;system information dialog<br>+tap weather icon-&gt;forecast<br>+tap Hour-&gt;launch anything!(more coming)<br>+tap Minutes-&gt;launch anything!</p><p>Widgets on Android work a bit differently than a normal application. Unlike regular programs they don't just install themselves in the application tray so you have to add them manually. They will not open or launch.<br>Here's how to add a widget on your Android home screen.</p><p>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger.<br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets.<br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device.<br>4.Select the clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>"Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.</p><p>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Skins: Check our website for help, and send to us your creations.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD Weatherzone  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Weatherzone" title="Weatherzone">Weatherzone</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="au.com.weatherzone.android.weatherzonefreeapp"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaNwo1EjMKLWF1LmNvbS53ZWF0aGVyem9uZS5hbmRyb2lkLndlYXRoZXJ6b25lZnJlZWFwcBABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Australia's favourite weather app, Weatherzone, gives you access to detailed observations, 7 Day forecasts, rain radar, BOM warnings and much more<p> Weatherzone uses Bureau of Meteorology forecasts and our meteorologists to produce accurate forecasts for Australia and the world. </p><p>Using data from the Bureau of Meteorology, our team of Meteorologists review this data to ensure you get the most accurate forecasts available in Australia.</p><p> Now with Snow &amp; Ski forecast, reports and snow cams! </p><p> What features are exclusive to Weatherzone?<br> Exclusive 3 hourly temperature, icon, wind and rain probability forecasts for the next 48 hours for all major Australian locations from Opticast<br> 7 day forecasts for 2000+ Australian locations for minimum, maximum temperature, icon, rain probability/likely amount and 9am/3pm wind.<br> National Radar and Lightning Tracker<br> Weather news stories from our meteorologist's<br> National Video forecast<br> 1000+ international location forecasts and observations<br> Exclusive Australian synoptic map with rain areas and amounts for 7 days (drawn by Weatherzone meteorologist every 12 hours)</p><p><br> What are other features of Weatherzone?<br> Real-time observations of temperature, wind speed and direction, dew point, relative humidity, pressure and rain since 9 am<br> Sunrise and Sunset times<br> Max UV rating<br> Pollen Forecast (for capital cities except Darwin)<br> Fire Danger Rating (where available)<br> Navigation Drawer<br> GPS search for current location<br> Past 24hours observations<br> Month to Date and Almanac<br> Dynamic animated backgrounds that change as the weather does<br> Real-time weather warnings <br> Animated radar from 58 locations around Australia<br> Animated National and State composite radars<br> Animated satellite of Australia<br> Can store and display UNLIMITED favourite locations<br> Three widgets<br>    - 4x2 Large w/ Clock<br>    - 4x1 Medium<br>    - 2x1 Small</p><p> Snow &amp; Ski <br> Australia's only 14 day snow forecast <br> Snow Reports <br> Snow Cams<br> Lift Status <br> Road Conditions </p><p> How do we make 3 hour forecasts?<br>Opticast uses real time observations and up to 10 global weather prediction models that are intelligently combined to build the most accurate high resolution short term forecasts available to the Australian public.</p><p> How do we provide more forecasts than the others?<br>We source data from the Bureau of Meteorology and then fill the gaps with our own team of professional meteorologists and in-house high resolution forecasting models. </p><p> Who is Weatherzone?  <br>Weatherzone is Australia's largest commercial meteorological organisation supplying most of Australia's media, electricity companies and other weather sensitive industries. Weatherzone uses Bureau of Meteorology resources and unique internally developed computer modeling to produce the most accurate forecasts available in Australia. We are a team of meteorologists and developers that are dedicated to providing innovative weather services.</p><p>## If you are having problems accessing the widgets please make sure the app is installed to the phone and not the SD Card. ##</p><p><br>Australian weather, Aussie weather, Sydney Weather, Melbourne Weather.</p><p>Support: http://help.weatherzone.com.au</p><p>If you have a Rings Digital Weather Clock  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Factory+Widgets" title="Factory Widgets">Factory Widgets</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="factory.widgets.bubbledigitalweatherclock"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaMwoxEi8KKWZhY3Rvcnkud2lkZ2V0cy5idWJibGVkaWdpdGFsd2VhdGhlcmNsb2NrEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Rings Android Digital Weather clock widget with Calendar, Time,weather &amp; forecast<p>Rings Android Digital Weather clock widget,size 4x2</p><p>It features:<br>============<br> 12 or 24 hour mode<br> Portrait or Landscape mode<br> Color choice for all information displayed on the widget<br> System Information as a pop-up window<br> Shows battery level on the widget<br> Shows Moon phase on the widget that is calculated automatically each day.<br> Current Weather conditions which include:<br>+Current temperature in Fahrenheit or Celsius<br>+Feels like Temperature<br>+Humidity<br>+Wind speed in Km or miles per hour<br> 2 Weather layouts on clock widget(user selected from configuration screen)<br> 2 Forecast layouts(user selected from configuration screen)<br> 4 Day weather forecast that includes for each day:<br>+High and Low temperature<br>+Precipitation percentage<br>+Weather description<br> Sunrise/Sunset times in either Forecast screens<br> 37 unique weather condition icons<br> Widget hotspots for interaction<br>+tap battery ring -&gt;return to configuration screen<br>+tap bottom left widget corner-&gt;popup system information window<br>+tap weather icon-&gt;launch forecast screen<br>+tap top half of time ring-&gt;launch anything!(user selected from configuration screen)<br>+tap lower half of time ring-&gt;launch anything!(user selected from configuration screen)</p><p><br>STEPS HOW TO ADD A WIDGET<br>==========================<br>1.On your Android home screen, tap any blank or empty area with size 4x2 and hold down your finger.<br>2.An Add to Home screen window will pop up. From that window, tap Widgets.<br>3.Youll be presented with a list of all the installed Widgets on your Android device.<br>4.Select the "Rings Digital Weather Clock to add to your home screen by tapping it.</p><p>Notes<br>=====<br>- "Time frozen/not updating"-&gt; taskiller killed the clock(exclude it from taskillers)<br>- When phone starts, clock starts in less than a min too.<br>- "Cannot find/Cannot Open/Cannot Launch"-&gt; read instructions above how to add widgets on your home screen, or step by step instructions in your application drawer.<br>-ICS widget not there -&gt;restart your phone, and the widget will be in the application drawer,under the tab widgets. Drag and drop the widget on a screen with empty space of 4x2.<br>ROM users-&gt; make sure the clock is NOT moved on SD card.<br>Widgets are not supposed to be on SD card. Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type "Buenos+Aires",remember the "+" sign -no spaces, don't include the quotes.</p><p>Email problems/suggestions<br>Check our website for more help.</p><p>EXCLUDE IT FROM TASKILLERS!!!<br>Be polite, this is a free app :-)</p><p>VIDEO HOW TO ADD WIDGETS<br>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DpMLF9b2aTQ</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type Phases of the Moon Free  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Universe+Today" title="Universe Today">Universe Today</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.universetoday.moon.free"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaJQojEiEKG2NvbS51bml2ZXJzZXRvZGF5Lm1vb24uZnJlZRABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">       <p>Love the Moon? Get this 3-D simulation, with Atlas, Monthly Calendar, Live Wallpaper, Widget and more! </p><p>Hold the Moon in your hand with this stunning 3-D simulation of Moon phases with data updated in real time. Swipe back and forth to move through the phases of the Moon. This app has all the data you need including Moon rise/set times, illumination, Moon phase name , zodiac location and the distance to the Moon, all in a beautiful, elegant app that's fun to use. It's even got a monthly calendar so you can see what the Moon will look like over the months.</p><p>It has all the same features as the Pro version, it's just ad supported.</p><p>     </p><p><br>See the current phases of the Moon with a beautiful 3-D simulation made by NASA satellites. You can even see the shadows change on the Moon as the phases change. </p><p> "Fantastic application for tracking everything you ever wanted to know about the moon. Beautifully designed as well. " - Art</p><p>This app shows you the current phase of the Moon, using a simulation of the lunar surface created by NASA's Lunar Reconnaissance mission during its observations of the Moon.</p><p> "Works great on my Samsung Galaxy Note running Android 4.0.4. The moon phase scrolling is very smooth. A great app that gives you "full control" of the state of the Moon!" - Chromeman</p><p>You can smoothly drag the Moon phase back and forth with your finger, or even "spin it" to quickly advance forwards or backwards. It's kind of hypnotic, and will keep a child entertained for quite a while.</p><p> Beautiful images of the Moon were made by NASA from data collected by spacecraft. Watch how the shadows on the craters change over the course of a month, and see the Moon's libration (wobble) as it completes an orbit around the Earth.</p><p> Installation includes a Live Wallpaper and a Widget so you don't need to run the app to always know what phase it is.</p><p> See the current date, distance, phase name, zodiac location and illumination percentage: updated in real time. GPS detection of your hemisphere and location to make sure the Moon looks right for you.</p><p> Swipe left and right to move forward or backwards in time to see what the Moon will look like in the future or past. It slides back and forth with "buttery" smoothness. Spin it faster or slower. You can even set it to spin through its phases on its own.</p><p> Pinch-zoom the Moon to see a full lunar atlas with spacecraft landing sites, mare and large craters</p><p> Need to find the next full Moon? You can click a button to take you to the next full Moon or new Moon.</p><p> You can also access a calendar that shows you the phase of the Moon for any date in the past or future. You can also see a monthly calendar of the Moon's phases.</p><p> Share your phase of the Moon images on all the popular social networks</p><p> Supports rotation to Landscape mode or Portrait mode</p><p> Press "Start Rotating" and watch the Moon rotate through its phases, all on its own. </p><p> Pinch to zoom the Moon in and out to reveal more details on the lunar surface, and then pan around with two fingers </p><p> Turn on a full lunar atlas, with dozens of labeled locations, including landing sites, craters and lunar maria. </p><p> See the zodiac signs so you can find the Moon quickly in the night sky </p><p>Developed by Universe Today. 265. It makes the daily weather essentials easily available and a simple access to deeper information while presenting it in a tasteful, lightweight experience that makes checking the weather enjoyable.<p>LifeHacker: "Overall it's a solid weather app, and a good competitor to Yahoo"</p><p>Android Police: "If you're into informative, yet minimal apps, then the company's newest offering, Bright Weather, should be right up your alley.</p><p>tested.com: "Right out of the gate it's probably one of the best looking Android weather apps, and it has some cool widgets (obviously).</p><p>PCMag: "Bright Weather is a Lovely New Android Weather App from LevelUp Studio</p><p>The beautiful design mixes stunning photography with minimalistic graphics as it tries to balance information, functionnality, simplicity and attractivity for your personal weather interests.</p><p>Sure you can just look outside to get an idea of whether it is cold, rainy or windy. But can you be sure not to get heavy rain later without checking the comprehensive weather forecast included in Bright Weather?</p><p>Bright Weather features many information and functionalities efficiently accessible:</p><p>- Android Wear support<br>- Simple weather overview with 24 hours forecast with temperatures and conditions<br>- Advanced weather conditions with todays hourly forecast, sunset and sunrise<br>- Six days weather forecast with details for the day and night<br>- Weather almanac enclosing temperature records<br>- Current Moon phase, UV Index<br>- Interactive Weather Radar Map featuring clouds, rain, snow, pressure, temperature and wind using data from OpenWeatherMap<br>- Take a picture and share your weather using the integrated camera feature<br>- Beautiful Widgets with an optional clock<br>- Daily updated background picture<br>- Get even more information with a direct access to Weather Underground website for you location</p><p>Smart notifications allows you to get notified for the weather before the weekend, or to create your own custom notifications like being alerted of a temperature change.</p><p>Bright Weather is brought to you by the creators of Beautiful Widgets and Plume, the awards winning applications available on Android.</p><p>Please let us know what you think, you can follow us on twitter href="/store/apps/details?id=com.aminor.weatherstation" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=com.aminor.weatherstation" title="Weather Station"> 268.    Weather Station  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=A-Minor" title="A-Minor">A-Minor</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.aminor.weatherstation"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaIwohEh8KGWNvbS5hbWlub3Iud2VhdGhlcnN0YXRpb24QARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  This app is perfect for amateur and pro meteorologists, outdoor enthusiasts, and anyone else curious about their environment.<p><br>Most Android devices still do not have a barometer, ambient thermometer, or hygrometer. See the (probably incomplete) COMPATIBILITY list below for devices that this app is useful with.</p><p>For those who desire more, consider donating by purchasing Weather Station Pro. PLEASE DOWNLOAD THE FREE VERSION OF WEATHER STATION FIRST to make sure your device has the sensors for the types of readings you want. </p><p>***IF UPGRADING FROM v1.3.1.8 OR LOWER TO v2.0.0 OR HIGHER YOU WILL HAVE TO UNINSTALL THE OLD VERSION AND REBOOT FIRST. A "-24" error code appears during update. This error doesn't affect the app and only appears when you try to update. It is recommended you uninstall the old version of the app and reboot your device before reinstalling. If you don't want to update you can disable auto updates for the app in Google Play.</p><p><br>FEATURES</p><p> No ads<br> Depending on device, supports: Ambient Temperature, Pressure, Relative Humidity, Absolute Humidity, Dew Point, Mixing Ratio, Heat Index, Illuminance, |Magnetic Field|, and Barometric, GPS, &amp; Density Altitude<br> Graphs with details including 24 hour and 7 day hi &amp; lo markers <br> Pro only: 14 day graphing<br> Pro only: 14 day hi &amp; lo markers on graphs also<br> Pro only: Multi-Series graphing able to graph any number of (normalized) reading types<br> Pro only: Ongoing Status Bar Notification (ideal for Temperature but can be used for any of the reading types in the range of -20 to 120)<br> Pro only: Sunrise/Set info<br> Pro only: Moon info<br> Notification alerts<br> Records set by your device<br> Share screenshots<br> Printing support (Android KitKat+)<br> Unit choices for temperature/dew point/heat index (F, C, K), pressure (mb, inHg, kPa, atm, Torr, psi, hPa, mmHg), absolute humidity (g/m, kg/m), mixing ratio (g/kg, kg/kg), and elevation/altitude (ft, m)<br> Pressure can be adjusted to mean sea level using the Altimeter Setting<br> Use GPS provided elevation/altitude for pressure adjustments<br> 5 widget types (4x1, 1x4, and 3 1x1) with 3 style choices (on Android 4.2+ these widgets are also available for the lock screen)<br> Widgets are highly customizable including text color and size<br> Pro only: Full size widget with icons<br> Pro only: Widgets have several color theme choices<br> Pro only: Light and dark application themes<br> Indicators for rising/falling/steady readings<br> 24 hour hi &amp; lo readings on main screen<br> Calibration of raw values output by sensors<br> Pro only: Experimental battery temperature based calibration for offsetting inaccurate ambient temperature and relative humidity readings<br> Export background readings to .txt files<br> Pro only: Unlimited Auto Logging of background readings with geo coordinates to .txt files<br> Localized numbers and dates &amp; times<br> Pro only: Settings and data from Weather Station v2.0.0 or higher can be transferred to Pro on first start</p><p>The 'About' section in the app has much more detail on how Weather Station works.</p><p>---</p><p>COMPATIBILITY</p><p>Devices with a hygrometer, thermometer, and barometer:<br>Samsung Galaxy:<br>S4 (IV)<br>Note 3 (III)</p><p>Devices with only a barometer:<br>LG Nexus:<br>5<br>4<br>Samsung Galaxy:<br>S4 Active<br>S3<br>Note 2 (II)<br>Nexus<br>Note<br>Nexus 10<br>Motorola:<br>Moto X<br>DROID:<br>MAXX<br>Ultra<br>Mini<br>RAZR MAXX HD<br>4<br>XYBOARD 8.2 &amp; 10.1<br>XOOM 1 &amp; 2<br>XT928<br>Sony Xperia:<br>Z2<br>ZL<br>go (advance)<br>active<br>HTC One (M8)</p><p>---</p><p>PERMISSIONS</p><p>*Precise location... for GPS elevation/altitude; Moon and Sun info and Auto Logging of coordinates<br>*Modify/delete/read USB/SD card storage contents... for exporting/logging background readings to .txt files; screenshots<br>*Prevent device from sleeping... for background readings and battery temperature based calibration services; the screen wake lock troubleshooting setting<br>*Run at startup... to restart background readings and the ongoing status bar notification after a reboot<br>*Control vibration... on a notification alert</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" Weather Now Forecast &amp; Widgets  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Hamster+Beat" title="Hamster Beat">Hamster Beat</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.hamsterbeat.wallpapers.fx.color.free"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaMgowEi4KKGNvbS5oYW1zdGVyYmVhdC53YWxscGFwZXJzLmZ4LmNvbG9yLmZyZWUQARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Bring your weather experience to the next level with the most beautiful and convenient weather app, ever.<p>This version is a fully functional 3-days trial. If you enjoy it, please upgrade to full version!</p><p>Weather Now is a fabulous combination of weather live wallpaper, which animates local weather, time of day and season on ANY custom background, and a set of beautiful weather widgets! </p><p>Based on an original idea, Weather Now lets you pick image from your gallery (or use one of embedded images) and put animation of your current weather right over it on your home screen. Easy-to-setup, customizable and beautiful weather widgets will also bring you all local weather info you need, including detailed weather conditions and 5-days forecast.</p><p>Gorgeous Weather Live Wallpaper<br> Local or custom weather animations over any image from your gallery<br> Animated sun, moon, rain, snow, stars, clouds, lightning, fog and frost<br> Stunning weather effects like raindrops or snowflakes on screen<br> Time of day, seasons and color animations<br> Cool color effects and photo filters like winter, spring, summer, autumn, sepia, b&amp;w and neon<br> Manual control of brightness, contrast, saturation and hue<br> Embedded image gallery<br> Slideshow<br> Special 3D panoramic mode<br> Easy-to-use settings with interactive preview<br> Daydream support<br> More features inside!</p><p>Beautiful Weather Widgets<br> Customizable backgrounds, colors and fonts<br> Customizable units, formats and application shortcuts<br> Home screen and lock screen layouts<br> Easy-to-use settings with interactive preview <br> Customizable weather update interval<br> Several different weather providers (including AccuWeather and Weather Underground)</p><p>Local Weather Forecast<br> Current weather conditions, RealFeel, high and low temp<br> Today, tonight and tomorrow predictions<br> Humidity, Pressure, Precipitation, UV, Wind Speed and Direction information<br> Sunset and Sunrise information<br> 5-days forecast</p><p>All weather effects can be tuned for your taste. Clouds, snow and rain depend on current wind speed and direction. Moon shows actual moon phase.</p><p>You can choose between real weather conditions or pick whatever you want right now. You can easily create your own live wallpapers such as snowfalls, rainstorms, lightning storms, frosted windows, rainy screens, sunny days with delighted sun-rays and so on. </p><p>All effects and animations can be applied to ANY image from your gallery, whether it is a real photo or your favorite wallpaper. Full HD ready, no quality loss!</p><p>Weather Now works well on both phone and tablet devices, uses low system resources and conserves your battery life!</p><p>HELPFUL TIPS</p><p>Widgets cannot be used when installed on SD, it's a system requirement. To add Weather &amp; Clock info, please open your apps, switch to widgets tab and search for Weather Now widgets there. Long-tap on a widget you want and drag it onto your home screen.</p><p>You can adjust Sun and Moon positions depending on your current background with your fingers. Drag them slowly!</p><p>Raindrops can be cleaned from screen by your fingers too!</p><p>Battery and RAM usage could be more than expected for live wallpaper because of settings with interactive preview and widgets. You do not have to worry about it, Android manages memory by itself.</p><p>In order to use automatic location, Google Location Service should be enabled in system settings. If you want to manually set your location but unable to find your city, try to type it in English, please.</p><p>PERMISSIONS EXPLAINED</p><p>COARSE LOCATION required to locate automatically and correctly animate current weather and time of day</p><p>FULL INTERNET ACCESS required to get local forecast</p><p>STORAGE required to support custom backgrounds</p><p>Please Rate &amp; Comment!</p><p>For any questions, suggestions or bug reports please email us at hamsters@hamsterbeat.com</p><p>Hamster Beat Team.<br>All delicious android apps by hamsters You assume total responsibility and risk associated with this application.</p><p>- Widget.<br>- Wait at least 48 hours before blue bar graph is complete.<br>- Click on "ALT" button for view relative and absolute altitude.<br>- Blue bar graph show variation of atmospheric pressure in the time.<br>- You can see the last 24/48 hours.<br>- Refresh time is about 1 hour for prevent battery drain.<br>- Refresh operation is very fast and optimized for minimal load <br>- Moon/Sun phase set/rise and direction<br>- Barometer needle is draggable (for initial forecast setup)<br>- QNH/QFE function (mbar only)<br>- LCD contrast/backlight<br>- Language customization <br>- Temperature &amp; Humidity (live for some device, such as Galaxy S4)<br>- Autosetup wizard<br>- Translation for : German, Spanish, French, Italian, Japanese, Korean, Russian, Czech, Polish, Hungarien .</p><p>If you want this apps on your native language, please send me email to alerosso@gmail.com <br>Feel free to send me feedback or request new features.<br>Build &amp; Tested on Samsung Galaxy S3</p><p>More INFO<br>https://sites.google.com/site/osbbarometer/</p><p><br>-- MOTOROLA XOOM 2 ME USERS NOTE --<br>Only Motorola Xoom 2 ME users report general failure. Enter GO Weather EX --&gt; Theme --&gt; Installed --&gt; choose the theme your desired --&gt; Apply<br>2. Choose pay with Google Checkout or Free with Getjar Gold<br>3. If you choose Getjar Gold, there will be several apps listed.  Just download whatever apps you want until you have enough golds to purchase the theme.<br>4. After purchase, go back to Installed --&gt; choose the theme --&gt; Apply </p><p>How to add a System Widget?<br>1. <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=mobile.application.forfree.earth" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=mobile.application.forfree.earth" title="Earth Viewer"> 348.    Earth Viewer  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=H21+lab" title="H21 lab">H21 lab</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="mobile.application.forfree.earth"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaKgooEiYKIG1vYmlsZS5hcHBsaWNhdGlvbi5mb3JmcmVlLmVhcnRoEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Animated planet Earth with live weather and satellite data.<br>Imagery included:<p>Climate Reanalyzer weather forecast<br>- World GFS Precipation and Clouds (+48h)<br>- World GFS Air Temperature (+48h)<br>- World GFS Air Temperature Anomaly (+48h)<br>- World GFS Precipitable Water (+48h)<br>- World GFS Surface Wind Speed (+48h)<br>- World GFS Jetstream Wind Speed (+48h)<br>- World GFS Snow Depth (+48h)</p><p>US Naval Research Laboratory, Marine Meteorology Division<br>- World Rainrate (-24h, generated every 3h)</p><p>METEOSAT 0 degree satellite<br>- Airmass realtime imagery (-24h, generated every 1h)<br>- Airmass realtime imagery full resolution (-6h, generated every 1h)<br>- Multi-Sensor Precipitation Estimate (rain rate) (-24h, generated every 15min)<br>- IR 10.8 (-24h, generated every 1h)</p><p>METEOSAT IODC satellite<br>- Multi-Sensor Precipitation Estimate (rain rate) (-24h, generated every 30min)</p><p>NASA GOES satellite<br>- Goes East Infrared (-24h, generated every 3h)<br>- Goes West Infrared (-24h, generated every 3h)</p><p>MTSAT satellite<br>- Infrared (-24h, generated every 1h)</p><p>SSEC<br>- Infrared low res global composite (-1w, generated every 3h)<br>- Water vapor low res global composite (-1w, generated every 3h)</p><p>Application features<br>- Interpolation between images<br>- Imagery selection from menu<br>- Live Sun light<br>- Bump mapping<br>- Data cache for offline use<br>- Double tap stop/play animation<br>- No Ads</p><p>Copyright and credit<br>CCI data has been obtained using Climate Reanalyzer (http://cci-reanalyzer.org), Climate Change Institute, University of Maine, USA.<br>NRL DATA has been obtained using United States Naval Research Laboratory, Marine Meteorology Division (http://www.nrlmry.navy.mil)<br>All METEOSAT images shown in the application are subject to EUMETSAT copyright.<br>For all NASA GOES images credit to NOAA-NASA GOES Project.<br>For all MTSAT images credit to Japan Meteorological Agency.<br>For all SSEC images provided courtesy of University of Wisconsin-Madison Space Science and Engineering Center.<br>For Xplanet cloudmap many thanks to Hari Nair author of Xplanet.</p><p>Limitations<br>On some devices application will not launch and crash report is seen. This is caused in most cases by low graphical card capabilities or low amount of memory of the target device. Application use OpenGL ES 2.0 and extensive pixel shader with multitexturing.</p><p>Time of CCI data is sometimes shifted back by one day. For exact time always the time in the texture is relevant. This limitation is caused mainly that it is not possible to get the date of the images from the cci-reanalyzer webpage without OCR and these images and not generated always at the same day time.</p><p>Application is distributed as local image viewer which is accessing public available content from internet on behalf of user. Data are internally cached and only delta is downloaded. There is no guarantee for the availability of the downloaded data and the application also works without internet connectivity. </p><p>Program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful, but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=org.emsc_csem.lastquake" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=org.emsc_csem.lastquake" title="LastQuake - EMSC Earthquakes"> 360.    LastQuake - EMSC Earthquakes  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=EMSC-CSEM" title="EMSC-CSEM">EMSC-CSEM</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="org.emsc_csem.lastquake"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaIQofEh0KF29yZy5lbXNjX2NzZW0ubGFzdHF1YWtlEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  ** WHY CHOOSE THIS APP? **<br>LastQuake is the Euro-Mediterranean Seismological Center (EMSC) official earthquakes app. This app is designed by seismologists for the general public, earthquake witnesses and the scientific community. <br>There are only about 1000 earthquakes of interest to the public each year but this is a tiny fraction of the total, 97% of the earthquakes around the world are detected only by instruments. Using direct access to the results of the EMSC seismic rapid detection tools, LastQuake presents primarily these significant earthquakes.<br>--<br>** WHAT IS THE EMSC? **<br>The EMSC is a non-profit scientific organization created in 1975 which federates 84 seismological institutes from 55 different countries. It offers rapid earthquake information to the public and international organizations.<br>The EMSC aims to reach the eyewitnesses and encourage them to fill in their earthquake questionnaire and send in relevant photos. These are added to publicly shared data about each event and help to assess earthquakes impacts.<br>--<br>** MAIN FEATURES **<br>* Real time data <br>* Significant earthquakes list (earthquakes known to be felt as detected by the EMSC seismic rapid detection tools)<br>* Near Me earthquakes list (customizable)<br>* All earthquakes list (full list of the earthquakes around the world published by EMSC)<br>* PTWC Tsunami Info and Tsunami Watch displayed in the lists when applicable (by tsunami icon)<br>* Colors allow seeing at a glance the effects of an earthquake (8 levels including 2 for tsunamigenic earthquakes)<br>* Customizable date formats (UTC, time at the epicenter or time in your device)<br>* Customizable push notifications (destructive earthquakes, around me earthquakes)<br>* Details about each earthquake: depth, localization, main closest cities, population<br>* Social media sharing via all the social apps installed in your device<br>* See comments and pictures by witnesses<br>* EMSC map, street map, aerial map for each earthquake (zoom in/zoom out)<br>* Map of the seismicity in the region for each earthquake (data from the exclusive EMSC database)<br>* Global map of the earthquakes around the world<br>*===&gt; FOR PEOPLE EXPERIENCING AN EARTHQUAKE &lt;===<br>-- Fill in the rapid questionnaire to help seismologists: instant assessment of the earthquake by clicking an illustration<br>-- Your comment and/or picture published at the same time on the EMSC website and in your Twitter / Facebook <br>* No ads!<br>* LastQuake supports two languages: English and French<br>--<br>EMSC is a NGO. If you wish to support our organization, you will able to buy the paid version of the app available soon in this store. If you can help to translate this app in the following languages, please contact us:<br>-- Spanish<br>-- Italian<br>-- Greek<br>-- Turkish <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a href="/store/apps/details?id=com.opensignal.weathersignal" title="WeatherSignal"> 366.    WeatherSignal  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=OpenSignal.com" title="OpenSignal.com">OpenSignal.com</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.opensignal.weathersignal"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaJgokEiIKHGNvbS5vcGVuc2lnbmFsLndlYXRoZXJzaWduYWwQARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  WeatherSignal uses native phone sensors to measure local atmospheric conditions, which are then displayed on our live-updating weather map. Join the world's largest crowdsourced weather project.<br>  <br>Features:<br> Readout for all the sensors on your device (think Tricorder - but real!)<br> Widgets for temperature, magnetic, light, humidity and pressure sensors (if you have them)<br> Save all data to CSV - play with it however you like<br> Map of readings of other users and of your own, see averages within each map window, click on icons to see full readout<br> Manual reports<br> Tons of graphs (for geeks like us :))<br> Contribute to our maps (you can turn off sharing in settings) <br> Share data to help us improve the weather forecast<br> Looks great on tablets<p>Turn your device into a thermometer, barometer, lightmeter and hygrometer - depending on which sensors your device has - with this app your phone is  a mobile science kit!</p><p>What if my phone doesn't have many sensors?<br>We've teamed up with Hex3.co to provide support for their StormTag and StormTag+. These bring pressure, temperature, humidity &amp; UV sensors into a package that attaches to your keyring, never needs charging and sends data via Bluetooth LE. Get one now - from $20 on Kickstarter :) http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/jonatherton/stormtag-a-bluetooth-weather-station-on-your-keyri</p><p>Get the beta:<br>https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/100212178184385927394<br>  <br>By using WeatherSignal you become part of the world's most ambitious weather crowdsourcing project  helping to record weather patterns on a more localised level than ever before. We are working with numerous meteorological institutions, including the Univ. of Washington, Birmingham Univ. and the UK Met Office. Your readings help us improve weather forecasting for everyone! </p><p>Featured in the New Scientist and Scientific American! http://bit.ly/1aFY3Ls</p><p>*Thermometer readings are experimental!*</p><p>*** This app is experimental! Individual TEMPERATURE readings may be incorrect, but when averaged over many users we get reliable information for our community powered maps. ***</p><p>The app works best on the Galaxy S4 since it has the most sensors. Get a StormTag to add sensors to your phone.</p><p>The WeatherSignal app can measure:<br> Pressure (certain devices only)<br> Temperature (see note)<br> Light Intensity <br> Humidity (Galaxy S4 only) <br> Magnetic Flux <br> Acceleration (turn on in application settings)</p><p>This app features Google's Activity Recognition: monitor when you're walking, in vehicle, on a bicycle. Save the results to CSV and perform your own analysis/create maps, for example for quantified self.<br> <br>*** TEMPERATURE ***</p><p>Weve come up with an algorithm that translates battery temperature into ambient temperature  making your phone a thermometer. For each user this is approximate but there is a very strong correlation between battery and ambient temperature when spread over a crowd of users. If you are using a cell phone without an external thermometer then the temperature reading youll see is a battery temperature reading converted through our algorithm. Often the algorithm will get it wrong, but we've shown that with appropriate averaging and filtering, these readings correlate extremely well with external ambient air temperature.</p><p>The Galaxy S4, which has an ambient air temperature thermometer, may produce incorrect readings if the phone is hot due to use.</p><p>*** PRESSURE ****</p><p>Devices that contain barometers include:</p><p>Galaxy Nexus<br>Galaxy S3, S4, Note (1,2,3)<br>Nexus 4<br>Nexus 10<br>Xoom<br>RAZR MAXX HD<br>Xiaomi MI-2</p><p>Units available:<br>millibars/hPa inches of mercury aka Hg or inches H<br>centigrade/celsius and Fahrenheit</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" Move it back to the phone storage.</p><p>Weather hint: For world destinations with two words in the name, type in the box the words with a plus sign.<br>For example "Buenos Aires" type Pair that with the latest news and videos, detailed radar maps including our satellite and radar, traffic flow and lightning maps, and users have access to more content than ever before. When active weather systems hit, the app features location-based weather warnings and alerts. Users can also view our live stream video to keep up to date with breaking news about the latest storms. </p><p>Key features:<br> - Detailed weather forecasts including current, short term, long term, hourly forecasts and 14 day trends<br> - Severe weather and storm alerts to notify you when a storm is heading your way. Users will see a red banner on the affected cities and regions and can click-thru for more info<br> - Multiple map layers  including radar, satellite, lightning and traffic flow provided by Beat the Traffic in North America, and satellite and radar maps for the UK<br> - Follow-me functionality, automatically detecting the forecast within 1km of your location<br> - Available in English and French, based on your device settings</p><p>Tips for the phone app:<br> - Tap the weather icon to get more forecast data, like wind speed and direction, humidity, cloud ceiling and more<br> - The icon on the top left provides a simple list (menu) of all the content available on the app, as well as app settings <br> - Right and left draw for easy navigation. The right draw allows users to add a location or to scroll between saved locations, while the left draw allows you to select various sections of the app<br> - Tap the weather icon to get more forecast data, like wind speed and direction, humidity, cloud ceiling and more<br> - Pull the screen down to refresh the data</p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" wetter.info  genau mein Wetter<p>Mit der kostenlosen wetter.info App jederzeit und berall ber das aktuelle Wetter und die Wetteraussichten von 1,5 Mio. href="/store/apps/details?id=b4a.zephyr" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=b4a.zephyr" title="Zephyrus Wind Speed Meter"> 408.    Zephyrus Wind Speed Meter  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Gaia+Consulting" title="Gaia Consulting">Gaia Consulting</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="b4a.zephyr"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaFAoSEhAKCmI0YS56ZXBoeXIQARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  This application brings the functionalities of an Anemometer (max 20 m/s)  to your phone.<p>Dynamic and Average wind speed measuring modes with real time charts, wind direction display (compass).</p><p>Suitable for any winter and summer windsport!</p><p><br>&gt;&gt;Quick start<br>The application relies on the mobile microphone signal. To achieve the best results consider the following:<br>1)  Easy calibration (only the first time): Some mobiles are automatically calibrated in the first installation phase. For details see the calibration section of the user manual<br>2) avoid measurement in presence of loud noises (heavy traffic,motorbikes, trucks, loud talking,shots)<br>3) keep your fingers away from the mobile microphone (hold it by the top) and keep it in vertical position<br>4) orient the back of the phone in the direction of the wind (keeping the display in front of you)<br>5) click on one of the function buttons</p><p><br>&gt;&gt;Troubleshooting<br>1) Wrong calibration: You must set the Noise level: see the User's Guide calibration section.<br>2) Attenuation on mobile mic: your measurements never reach the thereshold blue line. Restart android.<br>3) The application is sensible to low level talking (at a distance &gt; 50 cm from the mic): go in the settings menu and disable ACG (check on). <br>4)  No signals detected below 1 m/s or over 20 m/s: the smart phone microphones do not work under/over a specific pressure. </p><p>Read the embedded User Guide: for any info or troubleshooting you can contact us at support@gaiacons.com.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=b4a.zephyr" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a> 411.    Barometer Altimeter DashClock  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=baggus" title="baggus">baggus</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="pl.baggus.barometr"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaHAoaEhgKEnBsLmJhZ2d1cy5iYXJvbWV0chABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Make use of the built-in sensors of your device!<p>Features:</p><p>- Barometer, Altimeter and Hygrometer<br>-  Fully customizable (Now you can change colors of almost everything)<br>-  Charts<br>- Widget with trends<br>- DashClock support<br>-  Uses built-in sensors<br>-  Multiple units supported (Pressure - hPa, mmHg. inHg, mbar, atm. Altitude - meters, feet)<br>-  Internet connection is required only for providing  better accuracy of the altimeter (but only downloads data when you want to - there is no background data usage)<br>-  Data exporting to a .csv file (supported by MS Excel etc.)<br>- Calibration<br>-  NO ADS</p><p>Some usage tips:</p><p>- QNH can be changed using volume buttons (short click, long click)</p><p>- Go to altimeter settings, locate and set nearest airport. It provides more accuracy of the altimeter.</p><p>- DashClock users  DC refreshes itself about once an hour. After installing the Barometer app, enabling pressure tracking and adding barometer to a DC widget, please wait a while(up to an hour) until it starts displaying correct pressure (instead of 000). Pressure tracking service of the Barometer app does not start immediately. It is synced with other services running on Your device to preserve battery.  </p><p> - Widgets (normal, not DashClock Extension) refresh with a frequency set by Pressure Tracking Interval (in app settings). It is possible to refresh widgets manually without enabled pressure tracking option (but without displaying trends). To do so, please set widget click action to 'Refresh widget'.</p><p>- If you want to have a fully transparent widget background - slide the opacity bar to the far left (it doesn't matter what color it is)</p><p>- If you calibrate your barometer to show reduced pressure - disable the 'Use barometer calibration' option in Altimeter Settings.</p><p>Supported languages  English, Polish, Dutch Spanish and Germn. If you want to add more translations  please feel free to contact me. </p><p>For those who don't see this app in GooglePlay on their devices(CM users - I'm talking to you). href="/store/apps/details?id=com.sailgrib" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=com.sailgrib" title="Marine Weather | SailGrib Free"> 413.    Marine Weather | SailGrib Free  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=SailGrib" title="SailGrib">SailGrib</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.sailgrib"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaFgoUEhIKDGNvbS5zYWlsZ3JpYhABGAM=" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  YACHTING WORLD - "IMPRESSIVE" - July 2014<br>CRUISING WORLD -  APP OF THE MONTH - February 2013<p>Sailing weather and tides forecast maps designed for and by sailors.</p><p>With SailGrib, enjoy viewing weather and tide forecast on your Android device. <br>Select the map that you want to get data for<br>- request the grib file, download it and view its data on SailGrib.<br>- tide calculations are done directly on your device, no need for an internet connexion</p><p><br>The area selection is very simple as SailGrib uses maps.<br>The data request is done through SailGrib, Saildocs,Great Circle. SailGrib gets grib files by direct download or through an email exchange.</p><p>Features<br>- choose a map and overlay weather forecast data,<br>- download data using the best Grib files providers : SailGrib, Great Circle, Saildocs, MeteoConsult,...<br>- specify the request to your needs,<br>- request can be adjusted to match a maximum file size<br>- can be used with satellite phone email services like XGate with optimizer, the Iiridium Go or the AxcessPoint.<br>- offlline maps capability combined with satellite mail allows usage at sea.<br>- view weather overlays together on the same map</p><p>With SailGrib, you can download and view the following data:<br>- Wind (10m above sea level)<br>- Pressure (reduced to mean sea level)<br>- Precipitation (accumulated over 6 hours)<br>- Total cloud cover<br>- Air Temperature ( 2m above ground)<br>- Wave (significant wave height, mean wave direction and period)<br>- CAPE<br>- Tidal or oceanic currents</p><p>With SailGrib, you can specify the following parameters for your grib file request:<br>- grib provider : SailGrib, Great Circle, SailDocs, MeteoConsult, GMN, ....<br>- request method : direct download (SailGrib, Great Circle, MeteoConsult, GMN) or email (Great Circle and SailDocs)<br>- grid resolution: from very high resolution to 2.5<br>- time step between forecasts :from 1 hour to 12 hours depending on models<br>- number of days for the forecast: from 1 to 14 depending on model<br>- maximum file size. SailGrib estimates the size of the grib file you request and adjust the grid resolution and the time step to make sure your file will size be lower than your set limit.</p><p>With SailGrib, you can view the following data:<br>- Windbarbs<br>- Isobars<br>- Precipitation maps<br>- Cloud cover maps<br>- Temperature maps<br>- Waves maps and arrows<br>- CAPE map<br>- Currents</p><p>Tide forecast are not official and are for reference purpose only.<br>Grib files are computer-generated forecast files which are sent without review, and are offered on an as-is basis. There is no assurance that the data is accurate or correct. By using these data you agree to these limitations and assume all the responsibility for their use.</p><p>In february 2013, SailGrib was elected App of the month by the magazine Cruising World.<br>http://thesailingcompany.com/app/app-of-the-month-sailgrib</p><p>SailGrib uses the JGRIB Java GRIB decoder (jgrib.sourceforge.net) and OpenStreetMap (www.openstreetmap.org).</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=com.sailgrib" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </div> </div>     <div class="reason-set">  <span class="stars-container"> <a href="/store/apps/details?id=com.sailgrib" tabindex="-1"> <div Das Wetter in Deutschland  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=surfcheck.info" title="surfcheck.info">surfcheck.info</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="com.wetter.in.de"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaGgoYEhYKEGNvbS53ZXR0ZXIuaW4uZGUQARgD" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  Stay up to date with the current weather conditions in Germany - and in the world via the Weather station widget.<p>Das Wetter in Deutschland now contains more than 27 maps, forecasts and other items!</p><p>- Forecasts for today, this evening and tomorrow<br>- Satellite images (visible light + infra red)<br>- Detailed Wetterlage and text-forecast<br>- Maps showing the current temperatures and wind speed.<br>- UV prediction for today and tomorrow<br>- Animated weather map (several days in advance)<br>- Weather alarm + Coastal alarm<br>- Precipitation radar<br>- Rotate your device to view full screen<br>- Four app widgets bring live weather information to your home screen, including weather station widget working world wide!</p><p>Data is downloaded from the German national meteorological institute DWD. Due to the nature of this source, some content is written in German.</p><p>&gt; widgets only work when you run the app from phone memory, move to SD card will disable it.</p><p>Disclaimer:<br>We do our utmost to deliver you the best software and data available in the market, but of course we cannot guarantee the proper functioning or accuracy of both. Data sources can change over time. You can not derive rights from this information. By downloading and using Das Wetter in Deutschland you accept these terms.</p><p>Location:<br>The rough location permission is necessary to enable the Weather station widget to show you your local weather data. It is not used nor stored for anything else at all.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=ca.cumulonimbus.barometernetwork" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  <h2> <a class="title" href="/store/apps/details?id=ca.cumulonimbus.barometernetwork" title="PressureNet"> 422.    PressureNet  <span class="paragraph-end"></span> </a> </h2>   <div class="subtitle-container">  <a class="subtitle" href="/store/apps/developer?id=Cumulonimbus" title="Cumulonimbus">Cumulonimbus</a>   <span class="price-container"> <span class="paragraph-end"></span>   <span class="apps is-price-tag buy-button-container" data-doc-fetch-skip-cache="0" data-doc-fetch-vouchers="0" data-docid="ca.cumulonimbus.barometernetwork"> <div class="pon" style="display:none">1</div> <button class="price buy id-track-click" data-server-cookie="CAIaKgooEiYKIGNhLmN1bXVsb25pbWJ1cy5iYXJvbWV0ZXJuZXR3b3JrEAEYAw==" data-uitype="223">    <span class="display-price"></span>   </button>    </span>     </span> </div>  <div class="description">  By downloading PressureNet you are a citizen scientist helping make weather forecasts more accurate! <p><br>PressureNet is a network of crowdsourced weather sensors. We automatically collect atmospheric pressure measurements using barometers in new Android devices. We're sharing this data with scientists and researchers to improve weather forecasting. </p><p>PressureNet has been featured on BBC World Service, Wired Science, and MIT Technology Review:</p><p>BBC World Service: http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p014ypyj<br>Wired Science: http://www.wired.com/wiredscience/2013/01/android-weather-prediction/<br>MIT Technology Review: http://www.technologyreview.com/news/510626/app-feeds-scientists-atmospheric-data-from-thousands-of-smartphones/</p><p><br>Soon we'll provide you with a weather forecast based on your data! These forecasts should be significantly more accurate since the data is collected using smartphones - we can gather way more data about the atmosphere than ever before.</p><p><br>Until we make forecasts, we specialize in current weather conditions. Most apps show you the current weather at the airport, which isn't always relevant to you. PressureNet users alert each other of the weather, allowing us to build comprehensive maps of changing weather conditions on very local, relevant scales.</p><p><br>PressureNet supports all devices running Android 3.0+, though only tablets or phones with barometers will be able to contribute readings, see their pressure and use the widget.</p><p>Devices with barometers include:</p><p>Galaxy S3, S4, S5, S6<br>Galaxy Nexus<br>Galaxy Note, 2, 3, 4<br>Nexus 4, 5, 6, 10<br>Xoom<br>RAZR MAXX HD<br>Xiaomi MI-2, MI-3<br>Droid Ultra<br>Moto X<br>HTC One (M8)<br>..and others!</p><p><br>Features:</p><p>- NEW: Watch your contribution statistics rise as you help science</p><p>- Widget to submit current weather conditions (for map and animations)</p><p>- Animations of current weather conditions based on your submitted data!</p><p>- Interactive Google Map now includes weather graphics indicating current weather conditions, as submitted by you!</p><p>- Pressure drop/rise alerts: notifies you when your pressure starts to fall (indicating clouds/rain is coming) or rise (indicating good weather coming)</p><p>- Report the current conditions outside where you are - your data will show up on the map, in animations, and will help us validate our forecasts.</p><p>- My Data feature that shows your recent measurements graph and listing</p><p>- Export data you've submitted to a CSV file</p><p>- Settings to modify Auto-Submit options, change unit preferences, sharing preferences</p><p>- Widget to view your current barometer reading, submit readings, view pressure tendency</p><p>- Search for locations to quickly view pressure trends all over the world</p><p>This project is fully open source to foster innovation. The core PressureNet code is contained in our SDK so that app developers can easily integrate PressureNet inside their own apps. Check it out and email us if you have questions! PressureNet code on GitHub:</p><p><br>https://github.com/CbSoftware/PressureNet<br>https://github.com/CbSoftware/PressureNet-SDK<br>https://github.com/CbSoftware/PressureNet-server</p><p>We're always adding more features and would love your input. Visit our site at http://pressurenet.io or email us at software@cumulonimbus.ca</p><p>Keywords: PressureNet, pressure net, crowdsourcing, weather, barometer, sensor, hygrometer, forecast, barometer network</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p> <span class="paragraph-end"></span> <a class="card-click-target" href="/store/apps/details?id=ca.cumulonimbus.barometernetwork" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>  </div> </div>     <div
